<p>i have the following code.</p>  <p>if you inspect the log message, only the last option will be edited.  the handler@textarea does not use the correct option variable.</p>  <p>editing itself will work, but not each textarea for one attribute.  i created a working jsfiddle.</p>  <pre><code>    options_html = $('div');             var options = {label:{value:"123"},label2:{value:"456"}};     for(var x in options){         console.log(x);         console.log(options[x]);         console.log(typeof options[x]);         var option = options[x];         if(Array.isArray(options[x])){             continue;         }         var textarea = $("&lt;textarea class='form-control' rows='3'&gt;" + option.value + "&lt;/textarea&gt;");         textarea.on("keyup",function(){             console.log("UPDATE " + x);             option.value = $(this).val();             console.log(options);         });         options_html.append($('&lt;div class="form-group"&gt;&lt;label&gt;'+x+'&lt;/label&gt;').append(textarea));      } </code></pre>  <p><a href="http://jsfiddle.net/fmtuywtk/1/" rel="nofollow">http://jsfiddle.net/fmtuywtk/1/</a></p>